    INFO: 2026-03-04 12:27:29,495:               log.py:   20: Logging to /home/guillem/fragile/mdpdf.log
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:29,495:               cli.py:  103: /home/guillem/fragile/fragile_investor_whitepaper.md
    INFO: 2026-03-04 12:27:29,496:         converter.py:   14: /home/guillem/fragile/fragile_investor_whitepaper.md
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:29,636:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The Fragile Geometric Shell: Turning Any Base Model into a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:29,644:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: White-Box World Model
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:29,652:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Guillem Duran Ballester, March 2026
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:29,664:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: TLDR
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:29,726:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Fragile is a modular geometric shell that wraps any large base model -- VLA, LLM, or otherwise -- and converts it
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:29,733:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: into a white-box world model. It does this by inserting a hyperbolic encoder that decomposes the base model
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:29,736:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:29,845:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:29,938:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: opaque activations into a structured latent space with interpretable Mixture of Experts, where expert routing is
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:29,972:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: governed by Riemannian geometry rather than learned heuristics. The result: an interpretable, anti-collapse
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:29,979:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: representation layer that makes large models auditable without retraining them.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:29,985:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 1. The Problem
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:29,992:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: State-of-the-art deep learning is powerful but architecturally blind. Three concrete failures plague current systems:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:29,998:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Black-box representations.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:30,073:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Foundation models (GPT, RT-2, Octo, SmolVLA) learn internal representations that
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:30,092:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: work but cannot be inspected. When a VLA model controlling a robot arm makes a bad grasp, there is no principled
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:30,096:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: way to ask 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:30,101:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: why
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:30,197:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  -- to determine which internal feature drove the decision, whether the model confused two objects,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:30,231:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: or whether the error will recur under slightly different lighting. The representation is a high-dimensional feature
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:30,237:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: vector with no semantic structure imposed by the architecture.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:30,243:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Expert collapse in Mixture of Experts.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:30,603:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  MoE architectures (Switch Transformer, Mixtral, DeepSeek) scale
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:30,871:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: efficiently by routing inputs to specialized experts. In practice, a small fraction of experts captures most of the traffic
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:31,009:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: while the rest go dormant -- a failure mode called expert collapse. Current mitigations are ad-hoc: auxiliary
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:31,069:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: load-balancing losses, capacity factors, random routing noise. These treat symptoms, not the underlying geometric
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:31,079:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: cause. When experts collapse, the model loses representational capacity silently, and no amount of scaling recovers
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:31,083:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: it.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:31,088:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: No guarantees under distribution shift.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:31,385:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Robotics and embodied AI face a fundamental challenge: the deployment
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:31,577:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: environment always differs from training. A pick-and-place policy trained on a fixed table height will encounter
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:31,679:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: tables at different heights, objects in different orientations, and lighting conditions that never appeared in the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:31,712:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: training set. Without structural guarantees about how representations vary with input conditions, there is no
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:31,720:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: principled way to predict or bound failure under shift.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:31,727:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: No reward signal from action-only models.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:32,111:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Vision-Language-Action models (SmolVLA, pi0, OpenVLA) output
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:32,379:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: actions and nothing else. There is no reward, no value estimate, no critic. This makes it impossible to filter unsafe
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:32,533:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: trajectories before execution, plan ahead by evaluating candidate action sequences, detect subtle degradation in
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:32,601:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: policy quality, or transfer to new tasks via reward shaping. Standard solutions require either hand-crafted reward
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:32,617:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: functions (brittle, task-specific) or training a separate reward model from human preferences (RLHF -- expensive,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:32,623:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: data-hungry). Neither scales.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:32,628:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: No hard safety contracts in training.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:32,638:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  When something goes wrong during training, current systems offer a single
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:32,643:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: diagnostic: 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:32,647:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:32,652:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: loss went up.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:32,656:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:32,661:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  There is no way to determine 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:32,665:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: which
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:32,670:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  component failed, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:32,674:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: why
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:32,679:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  it failed, or 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:32,683:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: what intervention
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:32,715:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:32,727:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: would fix it. Soft penalty terms accumulate into a scalar loss and hope that gradient descent will sort things out.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:32,732:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: When it doesn
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:32,736:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:32,769:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t -- when an expert dies, a codebook collapses, or the dynamics diverge -- the failure is silent and
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:32,776:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: unlocalized. Engineers discover problems post-hoc by staring at MLflow curves.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:33,183:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: These are not separate problems. They are symptoms of the same architectural gap: current models have no
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:33,466:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: geometric structure in their latent space. Distances between representations are meaningless. There is no notion of
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:33,612:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: locality, curvature, or covariance. The manifold hypothesis -- that data lives on a low-dimensional manifold -- is
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:33,663:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: widely accepted but never enforced. And without structure, there is no principled way to extract rewards, enforce
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:33,672:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: safety invariants, or guarantee that the representation degrades gracefully rather than catastrophically.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:33,681:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 2. Executive Summary: What the Geometric Shell Delivers
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:33,689:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Fragile addresses all five problems with a single architectural intervention: we wrap a frozen base model with a 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:33,693:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: geometric shell
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:33,747:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  that imposes hyperbolic structure on its latent space. The base model is never modified -- it serves
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:33,755:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: only as a feature extractor. All interpretability, stability, and planning capabilities come from the shell.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:33,760:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Our current proofpoint wraps 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:33,764:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: SmolVLA
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:33,767:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (HuggingFace
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:33,770:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:33,777:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s 500M-parameter Vision-Language-Action model), training
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:33,780:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: on 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:33,783:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: LeRobot
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:33,813:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  robotics datasets. The same shell applies to any backbone that produces a fixed-dimension feature
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:33,819:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: vector -- LLMs, vision transformers, diffusion models (see Section 7).
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:33,824:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 2.1 Architecture at a Glance
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:33,829:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: flowchart TB
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:33,838:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     subgraph Frozen["Frozen Base Model (any backbone)"]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:33,849:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         INPUT["Observations\n(images + language)"] -->
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:33,859:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: BACKBONE["Foundation Model"]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:33,870:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         BACKBONE --> FEAT["Feature vector"]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:33,880:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         BACKBONE --> ACT["Action output"]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:33,887:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     end
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:33,898:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     subgraph Shell["Geometric Shell (learnable)"]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:33,909:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         subgraph Encoder["Geometric Encoder"]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:33,921:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:             FEAT --> PROJ["Project to\nPoincare ball"]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:33,933:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:             PROJ --> ROUTER["Distance-based\nchart routing"]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:33,945:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:             ROUTER --> VQ["Per-chart VQ\ncodebook"]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:33,964:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:             VQ --> SPLIT["Split latent:\n(chart,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:33,973:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: geometry,\nnuisance, texture)"]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:33,980:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         end
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:33,991:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         subgraph WM["Geometric World Model"]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:34,009:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:             SPLIT --> INT["Hamiltonian\nintegrator +\nchart
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:34,018:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: transitions"]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:34,028:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:             ACT --> INT
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:34,043:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:             INT --> PRED["Predicted\nnext state"]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:34,052:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         end
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:34,065:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         PRED --> DECODE["Decode to\nfeature space"]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:34,073:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     end
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:34,087:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     DECODE -->|"feed back as\nnext observation"| BACKBONE
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:34,100:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     style Frozen fill:#e8f0fe,stroke:#4285f4
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:34,113:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     style Shell fill:#fef7e0,stroke:#f9ab00
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:34,125:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     style Encoder fill:#e6f4ea,stroke:#34a853
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:34,138:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     style WM fill:#fce8e6,stroke:#ea4335
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:34,149:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The shell has two components:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:34,158:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:34,170:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Geometric Encoder
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:34,187:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Maps the backbone
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:34,196:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:34,448:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s feature vector onto a Poincare ball (a model of
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:34,578:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: hyperbolic space), routes it to the nearest expert via geodesic distance, and discretizes it through
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:34,598:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: per-expert VQ codebooks. The output is a typed latent: 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:34,615:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: (chart, geometry, nuisance, texture)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:34,656:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  -- four
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:34,676:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: components with distinct roles, not a single opaque vector.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:34,687:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:34,700:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Geometric World Model
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:35,107:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Predicts how the latent state evolves under actions using a symplectic
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:35,332:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Hamiltonian integrator -- an energy-conserving numerical scheme where forces decompose into
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:35,381:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: interpretable components. The predicted next state decodes back to feature space, closing the loop
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:35,396:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: for multi-step rollouts.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:35,411:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 2.2 What You Get
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:35,427:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 1. Interpretable, typed representations.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:35,442:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Every encoding decomposes into:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:35,453:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:35,463:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: K
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:35,482:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (discrete): Which behavioral regime is active (e.g., approach, grasp, lift)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:35,490:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:35,499:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: z
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:35,507:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:35,515:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: geo
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:35,533:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (continuous): Position on the latent manifold -- the geometric state
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:35,542:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:35,550:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: z
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:35,558:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:35,566:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: n
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:35,583:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (continuous): Nuisance -- pose, lighting, within-regime variation
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:35,592:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:35,600:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: z
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:35,608:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:35,617:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: tex
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:35,636:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (continuous): Texture detail -- architecturally firewalled from control
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:35,826:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: An adversarial probe with gradient reversal enforces that nuisance cannot leak regime-transition information. This is
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:35,845:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: not a soft penalty -- it is a causal guarantee on the factorization. See 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:35,855:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Section 4
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:35,872:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  for the full white-box component
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:35,882:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: inventory.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:35,896:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 2. Collapse-proof Mixture of Experts.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:36,937:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Expert routing is determined by hyperbolic distance to chart centers, not
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:37,639:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: learned logits. The exponential volume growth of hyperbolic space creates geometric energy barriers against expert
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:37,981:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: collapse -- merging two experts requires the optimizer to overcome exponentially steep geodesic distances. Nine
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:38,065:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: complementary mechanisms (geometric, information-theoretic, and causal) ensure that all K charts and K×C codes
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:38,079:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: remain active by construction. See 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:38,090:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Section 3
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:38,103:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  for the full anti-collapse analysis.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:38,118:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 3. Free reward model from demonstrations.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:39,073:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Fitting a Hamiltonian system to demonstrations is a form of inverse
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:39,365:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: optimal control: the potential that generates the observed trajectories IS the implicit cost function. The shell extracts
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:39,487:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: three complementary reward signals without any reward labels -- a continuous value landscape from the learned
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:39,523:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: potential, a discrete transition quality score from the Markov kernel, and a manifold proximity measure from
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:39,529:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: geodesic distance. No RLHF, no hand-crafted rewards. See 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:39,534:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Section 5
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:39,540:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  for the full reward extraction framework.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:39,547:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 4. A standalone discrete Markov model for free.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:39,653:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The causal enclosure probe doubles as an action-conditioned
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:39,708:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Markov transition kernel over the 256-state (chart, code) space. This ~50K-parameter MLP runs rollouts orders of
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:39,716:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: magnitude faster than the full world model and yields an explicit, inspectable transition matrix. See 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:39,722:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Section 3.2,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:39,726:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: mechanism #8
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:39,731:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  for details.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:39,736:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 5. Hard safety contracts.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:39,781:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  A runtime monitoring system of 60 typed diagnostics watches every geometric and causal
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:39,793:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: invariant. When an invariant is violated, training halts and localizes the failure -- not 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:39,800:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:39,806:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: loss went up
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:39,810:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:39,815:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  but 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:39,822:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:39,843:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: chart-observation mutual information dropped below threshold at epoch 47.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:39,848:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:39,853:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  See 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:39,858:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Section 4.4
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:39,863:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  for the Sieve
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:39,868:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: architecture.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:39,878:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 2.3 The SmolVLA Proofpoint
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:39,968:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: We wrap SmolVLA without modifying any of its 500M parameters. The frozen backbone produces a feature vector
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:39,982:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: per frame; our shell operates entirely in that feature space.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:39,993:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | What we measure | Why it matters |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:40,002:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:40,011:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |---|---|
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:40,018:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:40,048:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | State-timestep alignment (AMI) | Do the 256 discrete states discover
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:40,055:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: temporal task structure without labels? |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:40,059:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:40,070:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Code utilization entropy | Are all experts and codes active, or has the MoE
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:40,075:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: collapsed? |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:40,079:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:40,086:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Geodesic prediction error | Can the world model predict trajectories on the curved manifold? |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:40,092:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:40,103:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Energy
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:40,110:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: conservation | Is the Hamiltonian integrator stable? |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:40,114:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:40,130:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Generalization under shift | Does the geometric structure
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:40,136:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: degrade gracefully on held-out conditions? |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:40,211:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The pipeline: freeze backbone → extract features → train geometric shell in three phases (encoder warmup with 16
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:40,282:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: structural losses, world model warmup with geodesic diffusion, joint fine-tuning with gradient isolation) → evaluate on
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:40,288:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: held-out episodes. See 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:40,293:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Section 6
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:40,299:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  for the full experimental setup and 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:40,305:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Section 3
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:40,310:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  for the training pipeline details.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:40,316:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Early results from the current prototype
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:40,329:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  confirm that the geometric structure discovers temporal task phases
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:40,335:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: without any phase labels:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:40,349:      pdf_renderer.py:  235: /home/guillem/fragile/vla_latent_space_by_timestep.png, 2182, 2028
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:40,761:      pdf_renderer.py:  235: /home/guillem/fragile/timestep_per_code.png, 2146, 608
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:40,909:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 2.4 The Geometric MoE: Charts as Experts
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:41,016:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The core architectural innovation. In standard MoE, a learned router network outputs logits that select experts. The
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:41,028:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: routing has no geometric meaning -- it is a black-box function of the input.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:41,034:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: In Fragile, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:41,040:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: routing is geometric
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:41,048:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: . Each expert is a 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:41,053:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: chart
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:41,069:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  on a curved manifold (the Poincare ball). Each chart has a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:41,074:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: center $c
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:41,079:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:41,092:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: k$ that lives on the same ball as the data. Routing is determined by hyperbolic distance:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:41,098:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: $$s
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:41,103:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
