   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:41,222:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: where $d
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:41,226:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:41,231:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: {
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:41,235:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: \
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:41,243:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: mathbb{P}}$ is the Poincare ball distance and $
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:41,247:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: \
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:41,551:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: tau(z)$ is a position-dependent temperature derived
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:41,691:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: from the local curvature. Points near the boundary (high curvature) get sharp routing; points near the origin (low
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:41,709:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: curvature) get soft routing. Think of it like a confidence-aware gating mechanism: the geometry itself controls how
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:41,716:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: decisive the routing is.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:41,795:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Each chart $k$ has its own VQ codebook: a set of quantization codes in the ball. The encoder selects the nearest
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:41,801:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: code within the active chart, producing a discrete symbol $K$ and a continuous residual.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:41,806:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: What this means for anti-collapse:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:42,041:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  In flat space, two experts can be arbitrarily close in parameter space and still
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:42,403:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: compete for the same inputs. In hyperbolic space, the exponential volume growth means that well-separated charts
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:42,562:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: have exponentially more capacity than collapsed ones. The geometry creates an energy barrier against collapse --
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:42,575:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: like trying to merge two cities on opposite sides of a mountain range. The full anti-collapse system is detailed in 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:42,581:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Section 3
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:42,586:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: .
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:42,596:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 3. Anti-Collapse: Why Our MoE Won
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:42,601:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:42,606:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t Degenerate
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:42,829:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Expert collapse is the central failure mode of Mixture of Experts. In Switch Transformer, GShard, and Mixtral,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:42,917:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: collapse is fought with auxiliary load-balancing losses, capacity factors, and random routing noise. These are
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:42,931:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: engineering patches. They work partially and unpredictably. They have no geometric justification.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:42,942:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Fragile solves collapse through geometry. Here is how.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:42,950:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 3.1 The Collapse Problem
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:42,957:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Expert collapse
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:43,025:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  occurs when one expert captures most inputs and the others receive no gradient signal, effectively
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:43,036:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: dying. In VQ-VAE and VQ-GAN, the analogous failure is 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:43,043:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: code collapse
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:43,056:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : only a handful of codebook entries are
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:43,063:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ever used.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:43,070:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Standard mitigations:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:43,076:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:43,085:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Switch Transformer
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:43,093:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Auxiliary load-balancing loss 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:43,100:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: α · f_i · P_i
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:43,126:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  where 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:43,132:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: f_i
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:43,142:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  is fraction routed to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:43,149:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: expert 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:43,157:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: i
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:43,163:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:43,171:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: GShard
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:43,181:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Random capacity factor with overflow dropping
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:43,188:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:43,195:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Mixtral
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:43,205:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Top-k routing with softmax normalization
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:43,212:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:43,218:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: VQ-VAE
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:43,228:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : EMA codebook updates, codebook reset heuristics
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:43,240:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: All of these are heuristic. None of them guarantee that collapse won
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:43,247:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:43,296:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t happen -- they just make it less likely. And
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:43,308:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: none of them provide a geometric reason why experts should stay separated.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:43,319:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 3.2 Nine Anti-Collapse and Causal Integrity Mechanisms
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:43,356:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Our approach uses nine mechanisms that work together -- seven derived from the geometry of the Poincare ball, plus
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:43,366:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: two causal/temporal consistency mechanisms:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:43,374:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 1. Chart Diversity Loss
