   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:45,258:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: $$P(S
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:45,263:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:45,268:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: {t+1} 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:45,272:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: \
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:45,277:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: mid c
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:45,282:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:45,287:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: {
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:45,291:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: \
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:45,296:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: bar{t}}, s
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:45,301:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:45,306:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t, a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:45,311:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:45,315:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t) = 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:45,320:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: \
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:45,325:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: text{softmax}
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:45,330:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: \
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:45,335:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: left(
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:45,340:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: \
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:45,345:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: text{baseline
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:45,349:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:45,353:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: probe}(
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:45,357:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: [
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:45,362:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: c
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:45,366:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:45,370:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: {
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:45,374:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: \
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:45,378:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: bar{t}}, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:45,383:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: \
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:45,387:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: text{code
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:45,391:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:45,396:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: embed}(s
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:45,400:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:45,404:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t), a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:45,409:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:45,413:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:45,417:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:45,421:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: )
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:45,426:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: \
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:45,430:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: right)$$
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:45,435:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: This is valuable for three reasons:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:45,441:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  1 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:45,444:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Lightweight planning.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:45,498:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The probe is a small MLP (~50K parameters) that predicts discrete state
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:45,517:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: transitions. It can run rollouts over the (chart, code) state graph orders of magnitude faster than the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:45,521:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: full world model. For coarse task planning (
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:45,523:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:45,527:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: will I transition from approach to grasp?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:45,532:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:45,539:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ), the discrete
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:45,544:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: model suffices.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:45,548:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  2 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:45,555:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Interpretable transition matrix.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:45,576:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  By evaluating the probe over all (state, action) pairs, you extract
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:45,582:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: an explicit $K 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:45,587:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: \
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:45,592:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: cdot C 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:45,596:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: \
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:45,601:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: times K 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:45,605:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: \
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:45,720:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: cdot C$ transition matrix per action. This matrix is directly
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:45,766:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: inspectable: which (chart, code) transitions are likely, which states are absorbing, whether the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:45,774:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Markov chain is ergodic or has transient components.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:45,779:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  3 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:45,785:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Causal verification at deployment.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:45,892:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The accuracy defect (full probe accuracy minus baseline probe
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:45,926:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: accuracy) is a real-time causal diagnostic. If the defect is near zero, the latent decomposition is
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:45,933:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: clean. If it grows, $z
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:45,937:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:45,948:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: n$ is leaking regime information -- a sign that the encoder needs retraining.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:45,954:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The probe is a 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:45,961:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: first-class artifact
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:45,996:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : returned from all training phases, saved in every checkpoint (periodic and final),
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:46,005:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: propagated across phases (Phase 1
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:46,011:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:46,075:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s trained probe warm-starts Phase 3), and loaded for inference. The discrete
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:46,087:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Markov transition model is always available alongside the continuous world model.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:46,094:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 9. Zeno Loss (Routing Smoothness)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:46,101:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  -- Penalizes rapid chart switching:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:46,106:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: $$
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:46,110:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: \
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:46,115:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: mathcal{L}
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:46,120:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: {
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:46,126:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: \
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:46,131:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: text{zeno}} = 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:46,136:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: \
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:46,142:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: frac{1}{H-1}
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:46,147:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: \
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:46,152:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: sum
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:46,159:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: {t=1}^{H-1} 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:46,164:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: \
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:46,170:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: text{JSD}(w
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:46,175:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:46,181:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:46,186:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:46,192:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  w
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:46,197:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:46,202:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: {t-1})$$
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:46,208:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: where $w
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:46,212:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:46,245:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t$ is the soft routing distribution at timestep $t$ and JSD is the Jensen-Shannon divergence (symmetric,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:46,253:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: bounded). This prevents 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:46,257:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:46,264:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: chart chattering
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:46,269:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:46,449:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  -- pathological rapid switching between charts on consecutive frames that
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:46,518:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: destabilizes both the encoder and world model. RL practitioners will recognize this as analogous to action
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:46,530:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: smoothness penalties, but applied to the discrete routing variable.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:46,538:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 3.3 Why Geometry Beats Heuristics
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:46,550:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The fundamental advantage is that hyperbolic space has 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:46,558:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: exponential volume growth
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:46,576:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: . In the Poincare ball model,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:46,584:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the volume element scales as:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:46,591:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: $$dV = 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:46,597:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: \
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:46,603:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: lambda(z)^D 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:46,609:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:46,615:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  dz^1 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:46,621:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: \
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:46,627:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: cdots dz^D, 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:46,633:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: \
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:46,639:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: quad 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:46,645:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: \
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:46,652:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: lambda(z) = 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:46,657:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: \
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:46,664:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: frac{2}{1-
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:46,669:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:46,676:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: z
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:46,682:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:46,688:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ^2}$$
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:46,697:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: As points approach the boundary ($
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:46,703:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:46,709:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: z
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:46,715:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:46,721:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:46,727:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: \
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:46,733:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: to 1$), $
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:46,739:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: \
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:46,745:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: lambda 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:46,751:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: \
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:46,756:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: to 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:46,762:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: \
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:46,771:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: infty$. The boundary region of the ball has 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:46,780:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: exponentially more volume
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:46,788:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  than the center. Consequences:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:46,793:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:46,802:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Codes spread naturally.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:46,993:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The uniformity loss pushes codes toward high-volume regions (the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:47,082:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: boundary), where there is exponentially more room to separate. In flat space, uniformity loss fights
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:47,095:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: against the curse of dimensionality. In hyperbolic space, it is assisted by it.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:47,101:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:47,111:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Collapse is energetically costly.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:47,303:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  For two chart centers to merge, they must overcome the geodesic
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:47,402:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: distance barrier. Near the boundary, small Euclidean movements correspond to large geodesic
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:47,420:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: distances. Collapse requires the optimizer to push charts through an exponentially steep energy
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:47,427:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: landscape.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:47,434:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:47,442:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Hierarchical structure for free.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:47,589:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Trees embed isometrically in hyperbolic space (Sarkar 2011). If
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:47,639:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the task has hierarchical structure (e.g., grasp type → object class → task phase), the geometry naturally
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:47,650:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: accommodates it without explicit hierarchy engineering.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:47,659:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 3.4 Activation Strategy
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:47,673:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: All nine mechanisms are active from epoch 0, with two exceptions that use warmup schedules:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:47,683:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Mechanism | Activation | Rationale |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:47,689:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:47,696:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |---|---|---|
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:47,702:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:47,728:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Mechanisms 1-7 | Active from epoch 0 | All geometric
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:47,737:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: anti-collapse losses fire immediately |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:47,743:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:47,802:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Jump consistency | Linear warmup over configurable epoch range | Jump
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:47,816:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: operators require minimally stable charts before learning meaningful transitions |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:47,823:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:47,921:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Causal enclosure GRL (#8) |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:47,960:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Gradual strength ramp over thousands of steps | The adversarial gradient must ramp slowly to avoid destabilizing
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:47,970:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: early encoder training |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:47,978:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: This 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:47,985:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:47,995:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: all active, slow adversarial ramp
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:48,003:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:48,040:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  strategy avoids the complexity of epoch-based gating while preventing the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:48,054:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: GRL from destroying nascent chart structure.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:48,064:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 3.5 Quantitative Signature of Health
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:48,079:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The window loss provides a real-time diagnostic. During training, we monitor three quantities:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:48,084:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:48,091:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: H(K)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:48,100:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Marginal chart entropy. Should be near 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:48,106:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: log(K)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:48,114:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (all charts used).
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:48,119:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:48,125:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: H(K|X)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:48,136:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Conditional entropy. Should be low (router is decisive per input).
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:48,141:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:48,148:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: I(X;K) = H(K) - H(K|X)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:48,157:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Mutual information. Must exceed a minimum threshold.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:48,164:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: A collapsing MoE shows $H(K) 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:48,169:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: \
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:48,177:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: to 0$ (one chart dominates) or $I(X;K) 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:48,183:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: \
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:48,394:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: to 0$ (routing ignores input). Our system
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:48,525:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: raises an automatic penalty the moment either degradation begins, long before it manifests as downstream
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:48,541:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: performance loss. Per-chart code entropy monitors whether each chart uses all its codebook entries, catching the 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:48,547:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:48,554:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: silent death
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:48,560:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:48,571:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  of individual codes that global metrics would miss.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:48,580:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The bottom line:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:49,084:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Standard MoE systems treat collapse as a nuisance to be suppressed. Our geometric framework
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:49,334:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: treats it as a physical impossibility to be engineered away. The hyperbolic embedding provides the capacity, the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:49,393:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: distance-based routing provides the mechanism, the causal enclosure ensures the decomposition stays clean, and the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:49,405:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: zeno loss prevents routing instability.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:49,417:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 3.6 The Three-Phase Training Pipeline
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:49,432:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Training proceeds in three phases, each building on the previous:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:49,443:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Phase 1: Encoder Warmup
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:49,453:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (configurable epochs)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:49,463:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:49,504:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Input: sequences of feature vectors (temporal losses like causal enclosure and routing smoothness
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:49,515:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: require sequential data)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:49,524:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:49,542:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 16 loss terms, each enforcing a specific geometric, topological, or causal invariant:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:49,553:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | # | Loss | Purpose |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:49,561:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:49,570:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |---|---|---|
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:49,578:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:49,598:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 1 | Feature reconstruction (MSE) | Ensure the latent preserves input information |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:49,607:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:49,636:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 2 |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:49,653:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: VQ commitment | Standard vector-quantisation straight-through loss |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:49,661:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:49,692:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 3 | Routing entropy | Encourage peaked (not
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:49,704:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: uniform) chart selection |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:49,713:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:49,729:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 4 | Diversity | Prevent all inputs from collapsing to a single chart |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:49,737:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:49,777:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 5 | Hyperbolic
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:49,792:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: uniformity | Spread embeddings across the Poincare ball |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:49,800:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:49,827:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 6 | Radial calibration | Match distance-from-origin to
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:49,838:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: routing confidence |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:49,846:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:49,864:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 7 | Codebook spread | Maintain minimum pairwise distance between codes |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:49,873:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:49,906:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 8 | Chart collapse
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:49,919:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: penalty | Penalise dead charts (charts receiving 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:49,928:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: <
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:49,937:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  1/K traffic) |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:49,945:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:49,972:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 9 | Code collapse penalty | Penalise dead codes
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:49,983:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: within a chart |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:49,991:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:50,009:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 10 | Window loss | Enforce minimum mutual information I(X;K) between observations and charts |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:50,018:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:50,063:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:50,080:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 11 | Encoder-decoder consistency | KL divergence between encoder and decoder routing |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:50,089:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:50,144:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 12 | Jump consistency |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:50,153:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Ensure chart transitions are topologically coherent (warmed in) |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:50,158:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:50,182:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 13 | Soft-equivariant metric | Fiber-bundle
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:50,194:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: structure preservation |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:50,203:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:50,213:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 14 | Orthogonality loss | Decorrelate nuisance and texture components |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:50,222:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:50,287:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 15 | Causal
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:50,307:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: enclosure loss | Adversarial probe prevents nuisance from leaking (chart, code) state-transition info |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:50,316:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:50,365:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 16 | Zeno loss
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:50,383:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: (routing smoothness) | Penalize rapid chart switching between consecutive frames |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:50,392:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:50,417:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Output: stable chart structure with well-separated codebooks and causally clean latent
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:50,427:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: decomposition
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:50,439:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Phase 2: World Model Warmup
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:50,451:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (configurable epochs, encoder frozen)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:50,460:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:50,477:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Input: sequences encoded to Poincare ball trajectories (encoder is frozen)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:50,487:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:50,504:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: World model learns to predict next latent from current latent + action
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:50,512:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:50,526:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Geodesic diffusion supervision
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:50,656:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (default): Creates intermediate waypoints along the shortest path
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:50,719:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: (geodesic) between consecutive latent states on the ball. The world model is trained to match each
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:50,735:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: waypoint, not just endpoints. Same-chart pairs use geodesic matching; cross-chart pairs use chart
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:50,742:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: transition cross-entropy.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:50,749:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:50,759:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Additional losses: energy conservation, force decomposition consistency, potential smoothness
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:50,766:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:50,774:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Output: dynamics that respect manifold geometry
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:50,785:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Phase 3: Joint Fine-Tuning
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:50,793:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (configurable epochs, gradient-isolated alternating optimization)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:50,798:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:50,807:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Both encoder and world model trainable at different learning rates with separate optimizers
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:50,811:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:50,817:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Two-step alternating optimization
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:50,822:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  per batch, with gradient isolation:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:50,826:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  1 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:50,830:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Encoder step
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:50,838:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (world model frozen): Update encoder using all structural/causal
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:50,842:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: losses
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:50,846:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  2 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:50,851:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: World model step
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:50,880:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (encoder detached): Detach all encoder outputs from its
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:50,887:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: computational graph, then update world model on dynamics losses only
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:50,892:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:50,915:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The detachment barrier completely breaks the gradient path between components, preventing
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:50,921:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: dynamics gradients from destabilizing the encoder
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:50,925:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:50,970:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s geometric structure. Unlike PCGrad or CAGrad
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:50,985:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: (which modify conflicting gradients post-hoc), this is a hard architectural guarantee -- no gradient
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:50,992:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: conflict resolution needed.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:50,999:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,043:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The causal enclosure probe trained in Phase 1 warm-starts into Phase 3, so the Markov transition
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,051:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: model benefits from the full training history.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,057:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Why three phases?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,107:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The geometric structure (chart assignment, codebook topology) must stabilize before dynamics
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,114:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: can be learned on top of it. Causal and temporal constraints must be enforced 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,119:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: during
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,246:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  encoder warmup -- not
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,338:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: introduced later -- to prevent Phase 3 from reshuffling chart assignments. The gradient barrier in Phase 3 eliminates
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,358:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: catastrophic interference. This follows the mathematical structure: the base manifold must exist before you can
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,363:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: define dynamics on it.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,373:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 4. White-Box World Model: Every Component Has Physical Meaning
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,379:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 4.1 What 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,383:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,386:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: White Box
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,390:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,394:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Means Here
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,410:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Standard VLAs produce opaque hidden states. Our geometric shell produces a latent space where every component
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,414:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: has a named interpretation:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,419:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Component | Type | Meaning | Inspectable? |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,423:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,427:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |---|---|---|---|
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,431:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,444:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | $K$ (chart index) | Discrete | Which behavioral regime
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,450:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: is active | Direct readout |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,453:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,457:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | $z
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,461:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,464:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: {
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,468:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: \
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,483:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: text{geo}}$ (geometric coordinate) | Poincare ball | Position on the latent manifold
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,488:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Poincare disk plot |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,492:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,496:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | $z
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,500:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,510:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: n$ (nuisance) | Tangent vector | Pose, disturbance, within-regime variation | Tangent space
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,514:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: analysis |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,519:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,523:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | $z
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,527:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,531:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: {
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,535:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: \
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,542:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: text{tex}}$ (texture) | Tangent vector | Reconstruction detail only | Firewalled from control |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,546:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,560:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | $w$
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,566:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: (routing weights) | Simplex | Soft chart membership | Entropy histogram |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,570:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,583:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | VQ index | Discrete | Which codebook
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,588:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: entry within chart | Symbol table |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,592:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,597:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Enclosure defect | Scalar | How much $z
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,601:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,613:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: n$ leaks (chart, code) state-transition
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,618:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: info | Probe accuracy difference |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,622:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,627:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Discrete transition model | $K{
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,631:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: \
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,635:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: cdot}C 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,639:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: \
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,644:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: times K{
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,648:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: \
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,664:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: cdot}C$ Markov kernel |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,671:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Action-conditioned (chart, code) transitions | Explicit matrix extraction |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,676:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,690:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Zeno flip rate | Scalar | Rate of chart
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,696:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: switching between frames | Direct computation |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,701:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,706:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: texture firewall
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,711:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  is architecturally enforced: $z
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,716:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,720:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: {
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,724:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: \
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,729:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: text{tex}}$ feeds only into the decoder
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,734:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,776:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s texture residual path.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,796:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: It never enters the world model. This means dynamics cannot depend on reconstruction artifacts -- a structural
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,802:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: guarantee, not a training signal.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,809:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 4.2 The World Model as a Learned Physics Simulator
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,816:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The world model is not a black-box RNN. It is a 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,822:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: symplectic Hamiltonian integrator
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,853:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  -- a numerical scheme
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,866:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: borrowed from molecular dynamics that conserves energy by construction. Each prediction step splits into
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,872:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: interpretable sub-operations:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,878:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Leapfrog Integration
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,884:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (multiple refinement sub-steps per horizon step):
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,891:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Step | Operation | Meaning (RL analogy) |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,895:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,900:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |---|---|---|
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,905:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,909:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,914:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: B
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,919:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (kick) | $p 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,923:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: \
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,929:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: leftarrow p - 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,933:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: \
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,938:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: frac{h}{2}
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,943:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: \
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,948:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: nabla
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,952:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,956:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: z 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,963:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: \
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,970:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Phi
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,976:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,981:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: {
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,986:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: \
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:51,995:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: text{eff}}$ | Half momentum update from value gradient |
