   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:52,240:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:52,244:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Conservative force
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:52,247:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Gradient of the effective potential $
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:52,250:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: \
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:52,253:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Phi
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:52,255:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:52,258:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: {
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:52,261:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: \
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:52,288:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: text{eff}}$. Drives the agent toward
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:52,298:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: low-cost regions. This is the learned value landscape -- states where demonstrations spend time have
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:52,301:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: low potential.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:52,304:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:52,308:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Solenoidal/steering force
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:52,390:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : An antisymmetric field (enforced architecturally, like the Lorentz force
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:52,427:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: in electromagnetism). Produces velocity-dependent steering -- responsible for orbiting and cyclic
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:52,433:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: behaviors (e.g., repetitive manipulation motions).
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:52,437:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:52,440:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Control force
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:52,445:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Action-conditioned force that encodes the policy
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:52,448:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:52,452:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s intent in latent space.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:52,456:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Built-in stability
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:52,621:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Forces and velocities are bounded by learned scale parameters derived from the minimum
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:52,684:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: resolvable length scale, ensuring the integrator never takes steps so large that it leaves the manifold. RL practitioners
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:52,693:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: will recognize this as analogous to trust-region constraints, but derived from the geometry rather than imposed as a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:52,697:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: hyperparameter.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:52,700:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Chart jumps
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:52,875:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (regime transitions): When the system needs to change behavioral regime, a learned jump operator
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:52,954:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: teleports the state to the new chart center via a rotation on the ball, and momentum is reinitialized. Jump decisions
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:52,978:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: use both a supervised component (trained to match observed chart transitions) and a value-driven component (prefer
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:52,983:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: charts with low potential and short geodesic distance).
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:52,988:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 4.3 The Diagnostic Dashboard
