   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:53,172:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 4.4 The Sieve: Hard Safety Contracts
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:53,220:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The Sieve is a runtime monitoring system comprising 60 diagnostic nodes organized into typed families. Unlike soft
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:53,227:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: penalty terms that accumulate into a loss and hope for the best, Sieve diagnostics are 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:53,232:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: hard contracts
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:53,248:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : when an
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:53,256:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: invariant is violated, training halts or reverts rather than continuing with corrupted gradients.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:53,262:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Family | What it watches | Example diagnostics |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:53,265:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:53,268:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |---|---|---|
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:53,270:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:53,272:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:53,275:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Switching / Zeno
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:53,287:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Is the agent changing actions too
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:53,291:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: fast? | Chattering detection, jump rate bounds |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:53,294:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:53,296:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:53,298:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Compactness
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:53,312:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Are representations staying inside the ball? | Radius
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:53,317:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: bounds, chart usage uniformity, dead-code pruning |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:53,320:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:53,323:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:53,327:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Scaling
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:53,337:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Do updates stay in proportion? | Gradient norm
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:53,341:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: tracking, trust-region checks |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:53,344:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:53,347:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:53,350:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Coupling / Sync
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:53,360:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Are encoder and world model consistent? | Chart synchronization,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:53,364:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: information window bounds |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:53,367:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:53,369:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:53,372:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Value / Pathology
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:53,382:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Is the value estimate well-behaved? | Spectral gap checks,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:53,385:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Lyapunov descent verification |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:53,388:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:53,390:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:53,394:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Energy / Conservation
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:53,404:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Is the integrator conserving energy? | Energy variance
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:53,408:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: bounds, stability violation detection |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:53,412:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Key design principle: halt, don
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:53,415:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:53,418:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t penalize.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:53,422:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  When a diagnostic triggers, the system identifies 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:53,425:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: which
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:53,439:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  component
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:53,444:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: failed, logs the signature, and halts the update. This makes failures 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:53,448:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: localizable
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:53,452:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : each node answers 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:53,455:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:53,459:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: what failed,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:53,462:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: where, and why.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:53,465:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:53,490:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Each failure mode maps to a named intervention (gradient clipping for divergence, reduced
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:53,495:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: learning rate for oscillation). The mapping is deterministic, not heuristic.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:53,500:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 4.5 Comparison: Standard VLA vs Fragile-Wrapped VLA
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:53,507:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Aspect | Standard VLA (e.g., pi0, OpenVLA) | Fragile-Wrapped VLA |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:53,510:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:53,514:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |---|---|---|
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:53,518:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:53,522:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
