   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,410:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: unconstrained inverse RL: the curvature bounds the metric, stability constraints bound forces, and a smoothness
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,414:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: penalty regularizes the potential.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,419:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The result is a reward model that is:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,423:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,428:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Structured
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,447:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Three components (potential + transition likelihood + geodesic deviation) capture
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,453:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: different aspects of reward at different scales
