   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,461:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Interpretable
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,467:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Each component has a named geometric meaning, not a black-box scalar
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,471:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,475:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Free
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,488:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : No reward labels, no human preferences, no additional training -- all three signals are
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,492:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: byproducts of normal training
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,497:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,502:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Multi-scale
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,506:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : $
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,510:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: \
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,513:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Phi
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,517:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,520:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: {
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,524:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: \
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,545:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: text{eff}}$ gives continuous value landscape, the Markov kernel gives
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,551:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: discrete transition quality, geodesic deviation gives manifold proximity
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,558:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 5.4 Practical Usage: A Combined Reward for Planning and Safety
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,564:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The three signals combine into a multi-scale reward:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,568:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: $$R(z, s, a, s
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,572:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,576:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ) = w
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,580:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,584:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: \
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,588:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Phi
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,592:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,595:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  R
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,599:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,603:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: \
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,606:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Phi(z, K) + w
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,610:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,614:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: M
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,618:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,621:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  R
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,625:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,629:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: {
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,632:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: \
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,637:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: text{Markov}}(s, a, s
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,640:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,644:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ) + w
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,648:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,651:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: g
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,655:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,659:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  R
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,662:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,666:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: {
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,670:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: \
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,674:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: text{geodesic}}(z)$$
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,679:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Component | Scale | Speed | What it catches |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,683:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,687:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |---|---|---|---|
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,691:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,695:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | $R
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,699:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,703:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: \
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,713:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Phi$ | Continuous, per-position | 1 forward pass
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,718:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: through potential network | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,722:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,727:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Is this region of latent space valuable?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,731:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,735:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,739:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,743:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | $R
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,746:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,750:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: {
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,754:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: \
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,771:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: text{Markov}}$ | Discrete,
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,777:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: per-transition | 1 forward pass through small MLP (~50K params) | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,782:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,787:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Is this transition consistent with
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,792:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: demonstrations?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,796:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,800:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,804:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,808:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | $R
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,812:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,816:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: {
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,820:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: \
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,826:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: text{geodesic}}$ | Continuous, per-position | Nearest-neighbor lookup | 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,830:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,837:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: How far is this
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,842:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: state from anything demonstrated?
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,847:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,851:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,856:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: For trajectory filtering:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,880:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Before executing a candidate action sequence, roll out the world model and evaluate $R$
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,887:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: along the trajectory. Reject trajectories that enter low-reward regions.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,892:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: For safety monitoring:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,897:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Continuously evaluate $R
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,902:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,906:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: {
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:57,911:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: \
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:58,066:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: text{geodesic}}$ on the current state. If the system drifts
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:58,167:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: beyond a geodesic distance threshold from the demonstrated manifold, flag for human review. The hyperbolic
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:58,276:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: geometry makes this threshold meaningful: a fixed geodesic distance corresponds to an exponentially increasing
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:58,292:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Euclidean volume, so the threshold is naturally calibrated to the local density of demonstrations.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:58,304:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: For task progress estimation:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:58,368:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Extract the Markov transition matrix, identify absorbing states (task completion),
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:58,380:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: compute mean first passage times. This gives a real-time 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:58,386:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:58,394:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: percentage complete
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:58,400:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:58,413:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  estimate grounded in the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:58,421:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: demonstration statistics.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:58,435:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 6. Practical Proofpoint: SmolVLA + LeRobot
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:58,444:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 6.1 The Setup
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:58,452:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Our proofpoint wraps 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:58,457:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: SmolVLA
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:58,463:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (HuggingFace
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:58,470:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:58,501:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s 500M-parameter Vision-Language-Action model) with the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:58,511:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Geometric Shell, training on 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:58,517:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: LeRobot
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:58,527:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  robotics datasets (real robot manipulation tasks).
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:58,534:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Pipeline:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:58,539:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  1 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:58,545:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Freeze SmolVLA
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:58,556:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  backbone. Extract features from the final layer. Cache per-episode.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:58,563:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  2 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:58,572:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Train Geometric Shell
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:58,737:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (Phase 1 → 2 → 3): encoder warmup on sequences (with causal enclosure and
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:58,800:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: routing smoothness active from the start), world model on sequences with geodesic diffusion
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:58,814:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: supervision, joint fine-tuning with gradient-isolated alternating optimization.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:58,820:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  3 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:58,827:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Evaluate
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:58,837:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  on held-out episodes and varied conditions.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:58,847:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Why this is representative:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:58,857:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Requirement | How robotics delivers |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:58,863:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:58,871:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |---|---|
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:58,877:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:58,903:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Random elements | Stochastic contact dynamics, visual noise, object
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:58,912:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: placement variance |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:58,918:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:58,942:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | SOTA baseline | SmolVLA (HuggingFace/LeRobot) -- a production Vision-Language-Action
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:58,949:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: model |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:58,955:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:58,971:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Clear generalization metric | Train on N object placements, test on held-out placements and lighting |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:58,977:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:59,033:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:59,050:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Representative of target market | Robotics, autonomous systems, embodied AI are the path to revenue |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:59,059:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The key insight: we do 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:59,067:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: not
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:59,077:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  retrain or compete with SmolVLA. We 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:59,086:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: wrap
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:59,274:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  it. The frozen backbone generates features;
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:59,348:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: our Geometric Shell operates entirely in that feature space. This is the product: a geometry layer that makes any
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:59,363:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: foundation model interpretable, stable, and generalizable.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:59,373:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 6.2 What We Measure
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:59,386:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: We target three categories of measurable impact:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:59,396:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Representation Quality:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:59,403:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:59,415:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: State-Timestep Alignment (AMI)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:59,684:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Adjusted Mutual Information between (chart, code) state
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:59,843:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: assignments and timestep within episode. High AMI = the discrete state space discovers temporal
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:59,862:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: structure (e.g., different states activate at approach vs grasp vs lift phases) without any phase labels.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:59,870:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:59,881:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Code Utilization Entropy
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:59,888:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : $H
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:59,895:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: [
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:59,902:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: \
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:59,910:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: text{code usage}
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:59,917:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ]
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:59,924:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  / 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:59,930:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: \
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:59,938:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: log N
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:59,944:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:59,951:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: {
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:59,958:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: \
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:59,985:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: text{codes}}$. Should be near 1.0
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:27:59,998:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: (uniform). Values below 0.5 indicate collapse.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:00,005:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:00,015:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Radial Distribution
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:00,035:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Points should fill the Poincare ball meaningfully, not cluster at origin or
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:00,044:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: boundary.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:00,053:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Prediction Accuracy:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:00,061:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:00,072:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Geodesic Prediction Error
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:00,141:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : For each action sequence, the world model predicts the trajectory on
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:00,155:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the Poincare ball. Error is measured as mean hyperbolic distance:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:00,165:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:00,175:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: $$d
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:00,182:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:00,189:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: {
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:00,197:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: \
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:00,205:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: mathbb{H}}(z
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:00,212:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:00,219:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: {
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:00,227:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: \
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:00,236:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: text{pred}}, z
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:00,243:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:00,250:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: {
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:00,258:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: \
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:00,266:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: text{target}}) = 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:00,273:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: \
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:00,280:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: frac{2}{
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:00,287:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: \
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:00,294:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: sqrt{c}} 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:00,301:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: \
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:00,309:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: operatorname{artanh}
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:00,315:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: \
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:00,322:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: left(
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:00,329:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: \
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:00,336:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: sqrt{c} 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:00,343:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:00,350:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (-z
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:00,356:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:00,363:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: {
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:00,369:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: \
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:00,377:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: text{pred}}) 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:00,385:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: \
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:00,392:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: oplus z
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:00,398:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:00,405:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: {
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:00,411:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: \
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:00,419:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: text{target}} 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:00,425:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:00,432:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: \
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:00,439:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: right)$$
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:00,446:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:00,579:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: This metric is native to the geometry. Since radial
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:00,632:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: calibration places confident points (sharp routing) near the boundary and uncertain points near the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:00,643:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: origin, the geodesic metric is automatically 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:00,654:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: stricter where the encoder is confident
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:00,726:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  and more
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:00,757:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: forgiving where it is uncertain. This is a built-in uncertainty-weighted error metric that requires no
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:00,768:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: additional calibration.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:00,776:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:00,786:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Chart Transition Accuracy
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:00,800:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Cross-entropy on predicted vs actual chart transitions.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:00,809:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:00,818:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Energy Conservation
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:00,856:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Variance of the effective Hamiltonian across trajectory -- should be near
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:00,868:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: zero for a well-calibrated integrator.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:00,876:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Generalization:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:00,883:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:00,895:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Train on episodes with specific object positions/orientations
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:00,900:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:00,912:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Test on held-out variations (different positions, lighting, objects)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:00,917:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:00,947:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Measure prediction error degradation: geometric structure should degrade gracefully (not
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:00,955:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: catastrophically) under shift
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:00,961:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:00,980:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: State consistency: same task phase should map to the same (chart, code) state regardless of visual
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:00,986:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: conditions
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:00,994:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 6.3 Competitive Advantages
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:01,005:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Advantage | Mechanism | Measurable Outcome |
