   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:01,655:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | No hidden state assumption | Swap base model without retraining shell |
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:01,665:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 6.4 The Generalization Argument
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:01,678:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Why should geometric structure help generalization? Four reasons:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:01,687:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 1. Exponential capacity.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:01,968:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Hyperbolic space has exponential volume growth with dimension. A 16-dim Poincare ball
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:02,097:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: can embed exponentially more hierarchical structure than a 16-dim Euclidean space. New conditions (e.g., different
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:02,116:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: object poses) map to different regions of the ball without overwriting existing representations.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:02,127:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 2. Chart separation.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:02,437:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Each chart (expert) specializes in a behavioral regime (e.g., approach, grasp, lift). Under
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:02,526:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: distribution shift, the chart assignment may change, but the within-chart dynamics remain valid. This is like having a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:02,539:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: separate model for each phase, but with smooth transitions.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:02,549:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 3. Curvature-aware dynamics.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:02,758:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The world model uses geodesic flow that respects the manifold curvature.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:02,835:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Predictions follow the natural geometry of the latent space, not Euclidean shortcuts. Under shift, the curvature
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:02,848:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: changes locally but the integration scheme adapts automatically.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:02,860:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 4. Hybrid discrete-continuous updates.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:02,949:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Chart transitions (discrete jumps) and within-chart dynamics (continuous
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:02,965:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: flow) are unified in a single geometric framework. This prevents the catastrophic 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:02,972:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:02,981:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: mode switching
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:02,988:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:03,011:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  that plagues
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:03,024:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: models with separate discrete and continuous representations.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:03,039:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 7. Beyond VLA: The Broader Vision
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:03,050:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 7.1 The Architecture is Base-Model Agnostic
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:03,120:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The Geometric Shell is model-agnostic by design. Replace the backbone with any model that produces a
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:03,134:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: fixed-dimension feature vector. The same architecture works on:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:03,141:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:03,149:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: LLMs
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:03,220:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (GPT, Llama, Mistral): Wrap hidden states with geometric encoder. Charts become semantic
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:03,235:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: clusters. World model predicts token-level dynamics on the manifold.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:03,244:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:03,252:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Vision Transformers
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:03,307:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (ViT, DINOv2): Wrap CLS tokens or patch embeddings. Charts become
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:03,321:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: visual categories. Anti-collapse ensures all categories are represented.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:03,327:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:03,333:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Diffusion Models
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:03,340:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : Wrap the denoising network
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:03,346:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:03,384:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s bottleneck. Charts become generation modes.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:03,395:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Geometric structure prevents mode collapse in generation.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:03,403:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The key insight: 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:03,417:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the geometric structure is imposed by the shell, not inherited from the backbone
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:03,439:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: . The
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:03,451:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: backbone provides raw features; the shell provides meaning.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:03,461:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 7.2 From Single Agent to Multi-Agent
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:04,070:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The framework extends naturally to multi-agent systems. Each agent has its own chart assignment but shares the
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:04,399:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: manifold structure. Coupling between agents respects finite information speed -- interactions are causal (past light
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:04,525:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: cone only), and symmetries emerge naturally from invariance principles (value shift, mode rotation, feature
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:04,549:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: relabeling). Standard MARL algorithms (IPPO, MAPPO) are the infinite-communication-speed limit of this
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:04,557:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: framework.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:04,856:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The competitive advantages compound across domains: any base model (swap the backbone), no collapse
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:04,906:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: (geometric guarantee), interpretable (audit every force), stable (symplectic), sample efficient (factored latent), hard
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:04,915:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: safety (boundary constraints), and sim-to-real ready (no hidden state assumptions).
