   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:05,894:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Summary
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:05,951:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Fragile is not a new model. It is a geometric shell that makes existing models interpretable, stable, and anti-collapse.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:05,962:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The core insight: by imposing hyperbolic geometry on the latent space of any frozen base model, we get:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:05,967:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  1 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:05,973:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Geometric MoE
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:05,980:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  where routing has physical meaning (geodesic distance, not learned logits)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:05,986:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  2 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:05,990:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Anti-collapse by geometry
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:05,998:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  where exponential volume growth creates energy barriers against expert
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:06,000:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: degeneration
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:06,003:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  3 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:06,005:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Causal decomposition
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:06,044:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  where adversarial probes enforce that latent components carry only their
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:06,053:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: designated information -- and the same probe doubles as a standalone discrete Markov transition
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:06,056:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: model
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:06,059:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  4 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:06,063:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: White-box dynamics
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:06,100:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  at two scales: a continuous Hamiltonian world model for fine-grained
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:06,110:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: trajectory prediction, and a discrete Markov kernel for coarse-grained planning and interpretable
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:06,114:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: transition matrices
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:06,117:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  5 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:06,121:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Reward from geometry
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:06,176:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  where the learned potential, Markov transition likelihood, and geodesic
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:06,198:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: deviation yield a structured, multi-scale reward model from demonstrations alone -- no reward
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:06,203:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: labels, no human preferences, no RLHF
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:06,206:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  6 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:06,209:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Hard safety contracts
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:06,214:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  where violations halt execution, not reduce reward
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:06,262:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The practical proofpoint wraps SmolVLA for robot manipulation, demonstrating measurable improvements in
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:06,270:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: representation quality, prediction accuracy, and generalization on a stochastic task with clear evaluation criteria.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-04 12:28:06,276:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The same shell applies to any base model. The geometry is universal.
